    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nThe latency increases 4x per keystroke, i.e. the first 5 or so characters inserted feel fine, and then it takes a second, then a few seconds, and eventually it freezes.\r\n\r\nThe issue bisects to #24647.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Run `nvim --noplugin --clean -u repro.lua sample.lua`, where `repro.lua` is:\r\n```lua\r\nvim.opt.scrolloff = 999 -- not necessary, but just sets up the viewport\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('FileType', {\r\n  pattern = { '*' },\r\n  callback = function() vim.treesitter.start() end,\r\n})\r\n```\r\nand `sample.lua` is provided here: https://gist.github.com/llllvvuu/45cf25963ffeab3f88feec196a032953\r\n2. **(IMPORTANT)** resize your terminal so that `:echo winheight(0)` returns exactly 58 and `:echo winwidth(0)` returns at least 79. The issue will not reproduce if your window height is off by even 1.\r\n3. `/vue<CR>o`. At this point, the last line in the window should say \"on_initialized\", and \"taplo\" should be the 4th, 5th or 6th line. If not, resize your terminal again and start over.\r\n4. Type `foobarbazfoobarbazfoobarbaz = {}<ESC>`.\r\n5. If you were able to survive step 4 (i.e. typed 5 chars or less), you should observe that each time you press `<C-e>` or `<C-y>`, `LanguageTree:parse()` is called 4^(n+2) times, where n is the number of chars you inserted in step 4.\r\n\r\nNOTE: Don't call `:lua vim.treesitter.inspect_tree()` at any point. It will cause the issue to not reproduce.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nNo latency in typing.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-814+g2ca076e45\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nMacOS 13.4.1 - MacBook Air M1 2020\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkitty 0.28.1, Terminal.app Version 2.13 (447)\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-kitty, tmux-256color, xterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from repo\r\n\r\n### Flamegraph (click for interactive)\r\n\r\n![flame](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/5601392/084df3c1-9b89-41cc-98ed-00f541d1887e)\r\n\r\n",
